cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as follows."
authors:
  - family-names: Taylor
    given-names: S. P.
title: "RePAST: Revised Accessible Pipeline for Automated Transcription"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-03-20"
DOI: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19140616
abstract: >-
  RePAST is a modular Python pipeline that automates the transcription and 
  alignment of long-form audio for phonetic research. It integrates 
  state-of-the-art components—including OpenAI Whisper, PyAnnote.audio, 
  and the Montreal Forced Aligner—to transform raw audio into linguistically 
  enriched, time-aligned transcripts. Specifically designed to handle 
  non-standard dialects and sociolinguistic data, the system 
  prioritizes accessibility for researchers without computational training 
  and ensures reproducibility through a robust, local-first architecture.
keywords:
  - "forced alignment"
  - "phonetic analysis"
  - "speech processing"
  - "dialectology"
  - "computational linguistics"
  - "sociolinguistics"
  - "reproducibility"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/your-username/RePAST"
